RACE.RACE_TEXT: MALVERN RACE 1 2 1/8M Hurdle CR: N/A. Maiden Special Weight Purse 25000. TO BE RUN OVER NATIONAL FENCES FOR MAIDENS, FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Four-year-olds, 146 lbs.; older, 154 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TOTAL JOY (IRE) placed forwardly, sent to lead out of the final turn, lost left stirrup, prevailed with a late surge at the wire. GOLD CHARM (IRE) rated well getting and inside path, closed, led at the final hurdle, overtaken approaching the wire, just missed. IMPERIAL ASSASSIN (IRE) rated mid pack on an inside path and finished well. ABSAM was unhurried at the start and made steady progress. QUID was alway alertly, had a sizeable lead, then gave way and finished the race. BRAILLE stalked in second place, tired and was pulled up. MASTER MCGRATH was no threat, pulled up two out. KIYOMORI dropped back and was pulled up.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: MALVERN RACE 2 2 1/8M Hurdle CR: N/A. Maiden Special Weight Purse 25000. TO BE RUN OVER NATIONAL FENCES FOR MAIDENS, FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Four-year-olds, 146 lbs.; older, 154 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: WEBB led from start, challenged at final two hurdles, ridden all out in the stretch and won with a final surge. LOOK NORTH stalked the pace, ridden all out in the stretch and just missed. GOOD BOY (FR) rallied, was outrun in the stretch. KARL CARES rallied, was outrun in the stretch. FIT FOR A KING tracked the leader, going strong and even with leader when fell at the final hurdle. GIRL DAD fell early on in the race and was vanned off.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: MALVERN RACE 3 3 1/4M Timber CR: N/A. Allowance Purse 20000. FOR FIVE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A TIMBER STAKES IN 2023. Five-year-olds, 160 lbs.; older, 165 lbs. Non-winners of two races over timber, allowed 5 lbs.; of a race, 10 lbs. (Apprentice timber races not considered).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ELUSIVE EXCLUSIVE (IRE) settled in second, prevailed dueling with CRACKER FACTORY into the final fence and through the stretch. CRACKER FACTORY (GB) set the pace, was passed by GREAT ROAD on the second circuit when rider on GREAT ROAD misjudged the finish, dueled with ELUSIVE EXCLUSIVE into the final fence and through the stretch, losing by a neck. GREAT ROAD was ridden to the lead on the second circuit, misjudging the finish as there was one more circuit to go, lost many lengths circling back on course to jump a missed fence, continued on to finish the race being over 200 lengths behind.

ENTRY.NAME: Elusive Exclusive (IRE)
ENTRY.COMMENT: dueled into final fence and in stretch, prevailed

ENTRY.NAME: Great Road
ENTRY.COMMENT: misjudged the finish, lost many lengths circling back on course

ENTRY.NAME: Cracker Factory (GB)
ENTRY.COMMENT: dueled into final fence and in stretch, just missed

RACE.FOOTNOTES: AWAKENED stalked in second, rallied to lead coming out of the final turn, led over the final two hurdles and drew off in the stretch. WHO'S COUNTING stalked the leader, rallied and finished well. ETERNAL STORY (FR) rated well and closed well. MODUS OPERANDI (IRE) had a rail trip and gave an even effort throughout. SOUTH MOUNTAIN (IRE) traveled never far back and gave an even effort. HAIL TO THE CHIEF raced held up and had no rally. REALIST (GB) raced held up and had no finishing rally. BEE MAJOR led for two miles, then stopped and pulled up before last hurdle. GEARHEAD trailed and was pulled up two hurdles out.
